  "prompt": "I was 18 he was 40. He InitIally said to me that he wIll cut his private parts if i say no to marrying him. I married him. I am unhappy what do I do?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry that you're experiencing this situation. It's important to prioritize your safety and well-being. Here are some steps you can consider:\n\n1. **Seek Support:** Reach out to trusted friends, family members, or a counselor who can offer support and guidance.\n\n2. **Professional Help:** Consider speaking with a therapist or counselor who can help you navigate your feelings and plan your next steps.\n\n3. **Legal Advice:** If you're considering leaving the marriage, it might be helpful to consult with a lawyer to understand your rights and any legal implications.\n\n4. **Safety Plan:** If you feel unsafe, develop a safety plan that includes where you can go and who you can contact in case of an emergency.\n\n5. **Resources:** There are organizations that provide support for individuals in difficult or coercive relationships. Look for local domestic violence shelters or hotlines.\n\nRemember, it's important to prioritize your mental and physical health. You deserve to be in a relationship where you feel safe and happy.",
